*   **Submission 4 (The Galapagos Archipelago):** This entry is highly striking and unique, covering a wide range of species specific to the Galapagos. it captures rare behaviors like a woodpecker finch using a tool (Category i) and features a diverse array of wildlife from volcanic cones to the deep sea (Category iv).
*   **Submission 5 (The Coastal Rainforest to Kelp Forest):** This submission stands out for its beautiful composition and the clear depiction of complex ecological links between terrestrial and marine habitats. It features exceptional behavior shots, such as a sea otter using a tool (Category ii) and a spirit bear with its cub (Categories ii & iii), along with high-quality macro insets.
*   **Submission 10 (The Amazon Basin Ecosystem):** Among the many Amazon-themed entries, this one is the most comprehensive and visually engaging. It captures multiple instances of striking behavior and young animals, including a jaguar hunting a capybara (Category ii), a harpy eagle with a chick in its nest (Categories i & iii), and giant river otters with pups (Categories ii & iii). It also excellently represents people responsibly interacting with nature (Category vi).

Winners: 4, 5, 10
